# 副簽  
(pos:名詞)  
<explanation>  
yue:正式簽名之外，用嚟應付日常事務或者比較唔重要文件嘅簡化簽名；有時亦都係由代理人代為簽署嘅簽名（量詞：個）  
eng:an alternative or simplified signature used for routine or less important matters; sometimes signed by an authorized agent instead of the principal  

<eg>  
yue:份合約重要，唔可以用副簽，要老細親自簽正簽。 (fan6 hap6 joek6 zung1 jiu3, m4 ho2 jung6 ji5 fu6 cin1, jiu3 jiu5 sai3 kan4 san1 zing3 zi2 cin1 zing3 cin1.)  
eng:This contract is important, so you can't use a deputy signature — the boss has to sign it personally. [end of text]


